org.opendaylight.controller.protocol_plugin.openflow.vendorextension.v6extension

Class V6FlowMod

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openflow.protocol.OFMessage
      • org.openflow.protocol.OFVendor
        • org.opendaylight.controller.protocol_plugin.openflow.vendorextension.v6extension.V6FlowMod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class V6FlowMod
extends org.openflow.protocol.OFVendor
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class is used to create IPv6 Vendor Extension messages. Specfically, It defines the methods used in creation of Vendor specific IPv6 Flow Mod message.

      • writeTo

        public void writeTo(java.nio.ByteBuffer data)
        This method forms the Vendor extension IPv6 Flow Mod message.It uses the fields in V6FlowMod class, and writes the data according to vendor extension format. The fields include flow properties (cookie, timeout, priority, etc), flow match, and action list. It also takes care of required padding.
        Overrides:
        writeTo in class org.openflow.protocol.OFVendor
